news.title: UK house prices fall in 2023, to stay subdued next year, says Nationwide
news.para: Britain's housing market, which enjoyed a boom during the COVID-19 pandemic, has been hit by higher borrowing costs after the Bank of England pushed up interest rates in its battle to tame inflation.

news.title: China: Guangzhou R&F's co-founder resigns as CEO
news.para: Earlier this year, 70-year old Zhang admitted bribing a former San Francisco official and entered into a deferred prosecution agreement with U.S. prosecutors to avoid criminal charges, according to a court filing.

news.title: Industry experts expects about 10% rise in property prices in 2024
news.para: Real estate stakeholders expects the momentum to continue in 2024 and are predicting a rise in real estate prices across segments.

news.title: Housing sales sees 31% growth in top seven cities in 2023: Anarock
news.para: New launches across the top seven cities saw a 25% annual rise – from approx. 3,57,640 units in 2022 to approx. 4,45,770 units in 2023. MMR and Pune saw the most new launches, together comprising an nearly 54% share of total new launches in the year.

news.title: Real estate private equity in a crystal ball and a rearview mirror
news.para: The past three years have been a rollercoaster ride for private equity (PE) investments in Indian real estate, with consistent fluctuations but a steady upward trajectory overall.

news.title: Kochi: LED streetlight project to be commissioned in June 2024
news.para: Once the project is implemented, all the streetlights will be converted to LED lights thereby saving energy and cutting cost by almost 75%.

news.title: Phase I of Mumbai metro 3 to open in April 2024
news.para: Phase I is a 12 km long stretch and will offer connectivity to, both, domestic and international airport as well as Metro I (Versova-Andheri-Ghatkopar) at Marol.

news.title: PCMC approves Rs 1.1 crore for land measurement to mark red zones in Dehu Road, Dighi areas
news.para: The initiative follows the December 8 fire at an illegal sparkling candle manufacturing unit in the red zone in Talawade, which left 14 workers, mostly women, dead.

news.title: Ludhiana: Non-construction fee defaulters to get notices soon
news.para: According to officials, the defaulters owe at least Rs 60 crore outstanding amount to LIT. The LIT officials are currently preparing the list of such defaulters and will start issuing notices in January.

news.title: Why Gurugram civic body's building tax bills are coming back
news.para: Officials said the civic body recently sent 505 notices to defaulters to pay up their dues, but most of them claimed there were discrepancies in the data.

news.title: Bengaluru: One year on, land transport authority remains on paper
news.para: Urban mobility expert Satya Arikutharam said a year is too long a time to constitute an authority and make it functional.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Five months since cave-in, no walls yet around plots dug up for a mall
news.para: In July, a portion of the service road of Gaur Global Village Society in Crossings Republik, overlooking this pit on the mall site, caved in, posing a threat to nearby buildings.

news.title: Maharashtra government scraps affordable housing in special development zones
news.para: The notification reintroduces the low floor space index of 0.025 on NDZs and allows tourism development, educational institutions, ground-plus-one residential structures, IT parks etc.

news.title: Two key Signa divisions filing for insolvency in hit to real-estate empire
news.para: Signa Prime Selection filed for self-administrated restructuring in a Vienna court on Thursday, and Signa Development Selection will file on Friday, Signa said.

news.title: Indian real estate: The transformative journey in 2024 and ahead
news.para: The year 2023 gave a fillip to the upward mobility in India’s residential housing market. The Reserve Bank of India’s move to keep interest rates steady empowered homebuyers to invest in their dream homes, enabling a wider population to become homeowners.

news.title: Dubai’s red-hot property market is bracing for a slowdown
news.para: So far, the boom has been underpinned by an influx of wealthy investors such as Russians seeking to shield their assets, crypto millionaires and rich Indians seeking second homes.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation to disburse first instalment to beneficiaries
news.para: Affordable housing through credit linked subsidy under PMAY(Urban) is allowed for beneficiaries from EWS with an annual household income up to Rs 3,00,000 and house sizes upto 30sq.m.

news.title: Noida: NMRC clears Aqua Line extension plan, to be ready in 36 months after government nod
news.para: ​On Wednesday, Noida Metro gave a go-ahead to the 11.6km corridor that will have eight stations — most of them in residential sectors along the Noida expressway that has emerged as a housing hub.

news.title: Dehradun: Doon Valley draft notification out for public suggestions
news.para: The proposed changes include the preparation of plans such as tourism, grazing, master plan of development, and others by the state government with input from relevant departments.

news.title: Land use of facilities may not be fixed under Indore master plan 2041
news.para: It was proposed in the master plan that land use of different facilities including residential, commercial and industrial, will not be fixed. But permissions will be given based on width of the roads.
